The paper discusses the use of Echo State Networks (ESN) for time series processing and learning, which is a topic commonly studied in the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper also introduces a new type of ESN with a reservoir of product nodes, which is a novel approach to neural network architecture and could be of interest to researchers in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the performance of the product ESN on standard benchmarks for chaotic prediction tasks, which is a topic commonly studied in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the mathematical analysis of the product ESN, which could be of interest to researchers in the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
